Q3.notes:
* ''Onslaught'' goes on cooldown after the effect ends.
* '''Severum's''' attacks are not {{tip|projectile|intercepted}}, but the attacks from the {{as|off-hand}} weapon are during ''Onslaught''.
* '''Aphelios''' will also not perform the attacks while channeling {{si|Recall}}.
* If '''Aphelios''' is {{tip|taunt|taunted}}, he will still attack the nearest enemy.
* During ''Onslaught'', '''Aphelios' ''' {{sti|attack range|link=range}} is reduced{{ft|to 410|by 140}}and his attack commands instead issue movement commands to walk into the respective range of his target.
* ''Onslaught's'' name is modified based on '''Aphelios' ''' {{as|off-hand}} weapon:
** {{ai|Calibrum|Aphelios|Precision Onslaught}}
** {{ai|Gravitum|Aphelios|Binding Onslaught}}
** {{ai|Infernum|Aphelios|Incendiary Onslaught}}
** {{ai|Crescendum|Aphelios|Arcing Onslaught}}
* ''Onslaught's'' attacks stack {{tip|Energized}}, but do not apply any other {{tip|on-attack}} effects.
* {{ai|Crescendum|Aphelios}} will not deal damage if blocked by {{ai|Wind Wall|Yasuo}}, but the stacks will still be gained.
* Cosmetically, the ''Moonlight'' cost is consumed through the duration.

Q5.notes:
* The volley applies {{tip|area damage}} and the follow up attacks from the {{as|off-hand}} weapon deal {{tip|basic damage}}.
{{Effect at cast time start}}
*The hitbox also includes a very small portion behind '''Aphelios's''' character model.
* ''Duskwave's'' name is modified based on '''Aphelios'''' {{as|off-hand}} weapon:
** {{ai|Calibrum|Aphelios|Precision Duskwave}}
** {{ai|Severum|Aphelios|Resurgent Duskwave}}
** {{ai|Gravitum|Aphelios|Binding Duskwave}}
** {{ai|Crescendum|Aphelios|Arcing Duskwave}}
* '''Aphelios''' is locked out of declaring attacks until the volley of attacks have been resolved.
* The automatic attacks do not trigger '''any''' [[on-attack effects]].
** {{ai|Pix, Faerie Companion|Lulu|Pix}} does not increase the damage of the volley.
* The volley of attacks won't deal any damage, if they are {{tip|dodge|dodged}}, {{tip|block|blocked}}, or if '''Aphelios''' is {{tip|blind|blinded}}.

Q6.notes:
* ''Sentry's'' name is modified based on '''Aphelios'''' {{as|off-hand}} weapon:
** {{ai|Calibrum|Aphelios|Precision Sentry}}
** {{ai|Severum|Aphelios|Resurgent Sentry}}
*** {{tip|Heal|Heals}} '''Aphelios''' for any damage it deals.
*** Attacks cannot be intercepted by {{ai|Wind Wall|Yasuo}} and {{ai|Unbreakable|Braum}}.
** {{ai|Gravitum|Aphelios|Binding Sentry}}
** {{ai|Infernum|Aphelios|Incendiary Sentry}}
* The ''Sentry'' will stop upon colliding with {{ai|Wind Wall|Yasuo}}. It will be deployed in front of the wall.
* The ''Sentry's'' attacks can be {{tip|dodge|dodged}} and {{tip|block|blocked}}, but not missed from being {{tip|blind|blinded}}.
